The paper discusses physical layer attacks on closed-loop wireless networks, which are typically studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and network security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The attacks involve deliberate manipulation of channel state information (CSI), which is a key aspect of wireless communication and falls under the networked information (cs.NI) sub-category. The paper also focuses on multi-antenna systems, which are studied in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the impact of malicious users on system performance, which is a topic of interest in the social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
